🤖 *This is an automated response from Repo Assist.*

For C# users wanting element-wise operations with custom types, I've added `ZipInto`, `ZipAlignInto`, and `ZipInner` extension methods in a draft PR (branch `repo-assist/improve-series-zip-csharp-extensions`).

These give C# users a clean API for combining two series with a user-supplied function:

```csharp
// ZipInto — element-wise combine (both keys must be present):
var result = s1.ZipInto(s2, (a, b) => a + b);

// ZipAlignInto — with alignment and explicit missing-value handling:
var result = s1.ZipAlignInto(s2, Lookup.Exact,
    (a, b) => a.HasValue && b.HasValue
              ? OptionalValue.Create(a.Value + b.Value)
              : OptionalValue.Missing);

// ZipInner — inner join producing struct tuples:
var pairs = s1.ZipInner(s2);  // Series(K, (V1, V2))
```

This is more idiomatic than the `Zip(...).Select(...)` workaround (which produces `FSharpOption` structs in C#) and directly supports the custom-type arithmetic use case described here.

