I've implemented URL support for `Frame.ReadCsv` in a draft PR — this directly addresses the documentation discrepancy where the API said it accepted "file name or web location (URL)" but the implementation only handled local files.

The fix detects HTTP/HTTPS URLs and fetches content via `HttpClient`, then passes the result to the existing CSV parser. Local file paths are unchanged.

```fsharp
// Now works:
let df = Frame.ReadCsv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/user/repo/main/data.csv")
let df = Frame.ReadCsv("(example.com/redacted)

// Still works:
let df = Frame.ReadCsv("local/path/data.csv")
```

```csharp
// C# also supported:
var df = Frame.ReadCsv("(example.com/redacted)
```

